{{Use British English|date=May 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Joel Coleman | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = Joel Coleman<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/612828 |title=Updated squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=2 February 2018 |accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1995|9|26|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/joel-coleman-241122/ |title=Joel Coleman |website=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Bolton]], England | height = {{convert|1.98|m|order=flip}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/joel-coleman/308526/ |title=J. Coleman: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref> | position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]] | currentclub = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | clubnumber = 13 | youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2013 | youthclubs1 = [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] | years1 = 2013–2016 | clubs1 = [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] | caps1 = 43 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2016– | clubs2 = [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] | caps2 = 5 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2018–2019 | clubs3 = → [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] (loan) | caps3 = 16 | goals3 = 0 | club-update = 17:00, 6 November 2018 (UTC) }} '''Joel Coleman''' (born 26 September 1995) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{English football updater|HuddersT}} club [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]].
==Career== ===Oldham Athletic=== Coleman was born in [[Bolton]], Greater Manchester.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.oldham-chronicle.co.uk/news-features/10/oldham-athletic-news/98419/coleman-is-on-the-brink |title=Coleman is on the brink |newspaper=Oldham Chronicle |date=6 June 2016 |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref> An [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] youth graduate, he signed a two-year scholarship with the club in 2012.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.oldham-chronicle.co.uk/news-features/10/oldham-athletic/69126/gang-of-nine-out-to-impress |title=Gang of nine out to impress |newspaper=Oldham Chronicle |date=27 April 2012 |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref> He signed his first professional contract with the club on 18 June 2014, penning a two-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/news/2014/june/coleman-im-very-excited/ |title=Coleman: "I'm very excited" |publisher=Oldham Athletic A.F.C. |date=18 June 2014 |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref>
Coleman made his first-team debut on 17 March 2015, coming on as a 57th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Jake Kean]] in a 3–1 [[EFL League One|League One]] home loss against [[Milton Keynes Dons F.C.|Milton Keynes Dons]].<ref name=sb1415/>
===Huddersfield Town=== Coleman signed for [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] on 7 June 2016 on a three-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36470037 |title=Joel Coleman and Ivan Paurevic: Huddersfield Town sign duo |publisher=BBC Sport |date=7 June 2016 |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref> He made his debut on 26 December 2016, playing the entirety of a 2–1 win at home to [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]].<ref name=sb1617/>
He replaced the suspended [[Danny Ward (Welsh footballer)|Danny Ward]] for the first leg of the [[EFL Championship play-offs|Championship play-off]] semi-final against [[Sheffield Wednesday F.C.|Sheffield Wednesday]], keeping a clean sheet in the process.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39838350 |title=Huddersfield Town 0–0 Sheffield Wednesday |first=Ian |last=Woodcock |publisher=BBC Sport |date=14 May 2017 |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.examiner.co.uk/sport/football/news/huddersfield-town-not-appeal-danny-13005128 |title=Huddersfield Town will not appeal Danny Ward red card |first=Rory |last=Benson |newspaper=Huddersfield Daily Examiner |date=8 May 2017 |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref> Following Huddersfield Town's promotion to the [[Premier League]], Coleman signed a new two-year contract with the club on 30 July 2017.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40766166 |title=Joel Coleman: Huddersfield Town goalkeeper extends stay with improved terms deal |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 July 2017 |accessdate=24 July 2018}}</ref>
Coleman joined League One club [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] on 27 July 2018 on [[Loan (sports)|loan]] for the [[2018–19 Shrewsbury Town F.C. season|2018–19 season]], after signing a new two-year contract at Huddersfield with the option of a further year.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.examiner.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/joel-coleman-joins-shrewbury-town-14960119 |title=Joel Coleman joins Shrewbury Town on loan after signing contract extension at Huddersfield Town |newspaper=Huddersfield Daily Examiner |date=27 July 2018 |accessdate=27 July 2018}}</ref>
